<br>
Karas had a good point in his last post:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  If we drop it to 20, thats assuming there wont be a dearth of new guilds in the 46-50 range all contending for the calendar again..and that would be foolish as I see it....history can repeat itself  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
do you want an influx of people who are newbies to the planes, barely high enough, and know next to nothing about planes raids?  You will get new posting entities by lowering the number of planeables required, and I'm sure quite a few will be first-timers to the planes... Judging from responses in this thread, some guilds can do the planes with ease, but there are some that struggle despite meeting the requirements to post on the calendar.  The number of people struggling with the planes will increase if the number is lowered too far...<br>
<br>
Another thing - just because a guild has 40 planeables doesn't mean that all 40 willl show.  There's something called &quot;real life&quot; that interferes with most peoples' EQ time on a regular basis, so the number of planeables needed to post on the calendar needs to be higher than what is actually needed to clear the plane because it's very hard to get 100% attendance on raids, to put it mildly.   <br>
<br>
Cosimo Stormcaller<br>
