<br>
It was said that guilds whom can't meet the 40 member rule but might be able to meet a 30 member rule cannot handle the planes.  This really is not up to anyone to decide except for the tatical officers in that guild.<br>
<br>
It was said that people would come flame another guild for not helping them CR.  So?  It is no one's responsibility to help anyone else.<br>
<br>
I will assume that there is not a giant line for planar armor like there was back in the days before the split, the golems are not going to be taken down by any guild that can't handle clearing the plane anyway (much less dracholie and Cazic), and should the guild whipeout on a day where any of these mobs are up, you could easily set up some way of handling this.<br>
<br>
On Zeb there is no calander.  Most top guilds don't mind helping people, even unguilded, get one or two pieces for whatever epic because of the more valuable weapons to be had in Velious.  Many epics are completed, and generally when the mob is up something is worked out between leaderships.<br>
<br>
This is not a chest bashing event, I just think that the idea might actually be a pretty good idea.  The planes are not as important as they once were, I don't think that being a little more lax in the way things work on the calander would harm the system.  <br>
<br>
