<br>
We currently have several open days and/or guilds raiding each plane multiple times each month.  The rationale for the 40 member limit was so that guilds did not have to wait months between plane dates so if dropping the number of planeables to 30-35 does not cause a log jam on the calendar then we should consider it.<br>
<br>
The whole CR issue is really a non-issue. A guild new to the planes is going to need CR regardless of if they have 40 planeables, 30 planeables or 80 planeables. Even guilds that have been doing the planes for over a year require CR due to some bad luck so that is not going to change anything.  Also nobody said anyone is obligated to CR another guild so this should not be a major stumbling block.<br>
<br>
I guess my point is to get an idea of the impact of lowering the number of planeables will have on the calendar. If there is suddenly 40 new planeable entities then I would have to vote no to lowering it however if it amounts to a few new posting entities then there should not be a problem. <p><B><font color = Purple size =2>
